<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">

<head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8">
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
    <title>Url Shortner</title>
    <link rel="stylesheet" href="style.css">
    <script src="https://kit.fontawesome.com/23de7712d8.js" crossorigin="anonymous"></script>
</head>

<body>

    <header>
        <div class="title">
            <h1>&lbrace; Url Shortner &rbrace;</h1>
            <h3 id="about">About</h3>
        </div>

        <section>
            <div class="container">
                <form action="/shortUrl" method="POST">
                    <input type="url" name="fullUrl" id="fullUrl">
                    <button type="submit"><i class="fa-solid fa-link"></i> Get</button>
                </form>

                <table>
                    <thead>
                        <tr>
                            <th>Full URL</th>
                            <th>Short URL</th>
                            <th>Clicks</th>
                        </tr>
                    </thead>
                    <tbody>
                        <% shortUrls.forEach(shortUrl=> { %>
                            <tr>
                                <td><a href="<%= shortUrl.full %>">
                                        <%= shortUrl.full %>
                                    </a></td>
                                <td><a href="<%= shortUrl.short %>">
                                        <%= shortUrl.short %>
                                    </a></td>
                                <td>
                                    <%= shortUrl.clicks %>
                                </td>
                            </tr>
                            <% }) %>
                    </tbody>
                </table>
            </div>
        </section>
    </header>

    <main>
        <section>
            <div class="about">
                <p>A URL shortener is a tool or service that takes a long URL (Uniform Resource Locator) and creates a
                    shorter, condensed version of it. The purpose of a URL shortener is to make long, complex URLs more
                    manageable and easier to share.
                    URL shorteners are commonly used on platforms with character limits, such as social media platforms
                    like Twitter, where the number of characters is restricted for each post. By shortening a URL, it
                    reduces the number of characters needed to display the link, making it more convenient to share
                    within those limitations. A custom, or branded URL shortener, is when youâ€™ve connected your own
                    custom domain to a URL
                    shortener which acts as a base for all the short links you create. Instead of using a generic domain
                    such as bit.ly or rebrand.ly, you can pick your own.</p>
                <div id="close">X</div>
            </div>
        </section>
    </main>

    <script src="index.js"></script>
</body>

</html>